title: Ed Miliband Rules Out Deal With Scottish Nationalists
description: The Labour leader, Ed Miliband, made clearer on Monday what his strategy would be in the event of a hung Parliament: he would present a Labour minority government committed to Labour’s manifesto and dare the Scottish National Party and everyone else to vote it down.

title: Two Gunmen Killed at Anti-Islam Exhibit Are Identified
description: A law enforcement official said Elton Simpson of Phoenix was one of two gunmen killed after opening fire at an exhibit in Garland, Tex. Officials later identified the second gunman as Nadir Soofi.

title: Dean Skelos, New York Senate Leader, and Son Are Arrested on Corruption Charges
description: Mr. Skelos, 67, and his son, Adam B. Skelos, 32, are scheduled to appear in United States District Court in Manhattan to face complaints of conspiracy, extortion and bribe solicitation.

title: First Draft: The Chat: Ben Carson’s Announcement, Instantly Analyzed
description: Patrick Healy and Maggie Haberman digest the retired neurosurgeon’s entry into the Republican presidential contest by instant message.

title: Dave Goldberg, Silicon Valley Executive, Said to Have Died After Exercising
description: The 47-year-old chief of Survey Monkey, who was married to Sheryl Sandberg of Facebook, collapsed at a Mexican resort, a person close to the family said.

title: Police Start to Reconsider Longstanding Rules on Using Force
description: A small but vocal number of law enforcement officials are calling for a rethinking of axioms that have emphasized how to use force, not how to avoid it.

title: E.P.A. Emissions Plan Will Save Thousands of Lives, Study Finds
description: The carbon emissions standards, proposed last year for the nation’s coal-fired power plants, could prevent more than 3,000 premature deaths per year, according to a new study.

title: Nepalis in New York Improvise a Relief Effort for Earthquake Victims
description: The small but fast-growing population, despite a lack of well-established community institutions, has used technology and social media to help its homeland.

title: 2 With Ties to Christie Plead Not Guilty in Bridge Scandal
description: Bill Baroni and Bridget Anne Kelly face federal charges that they participated in a conspiracy to disrupt traffic leading to the George Washington Bridge.

title: Charlotte Elizabeth Diana Is Royal Baby’s Name
description: Many in Britain rejoiced on Monday after Kensington Palace announced that Britain’s new princess would be named Charlotte Elizabeth Diana.

title: Britain’s Campaign Finance Laws Leave Parties With Idle Money
description: Few countries combine Britain’s fascination with American-style politics with campaign finance rules so stringent that they might seem better suited to City Council races.

title: M.T.A. Chairman Asks New York City for More Than $1 Billion in Funding
description: The chairman, Thomas F. Prendergast, is asking the city to contribute $1 billion toward the construction of the Second Avenue subway line and $300 million annually to the capital plan.

title: Your Monday Briefing
description: Here’s what you need to know to start your day.

title: News Analysis: Campaign Coverage via Snapchat Could Shake Up the 2016 Elections
description: The question of how the fast-growing app could shape the election arose after it hired a CNN political reporter to lead its nascent news division.

title: First Draft: Bernie Sanders’s Brother Faces British Voters
description: Larry Sanders, 80, is running as a Green party candidate in Oxfordshire in Thursday’s general election.

title: Unsatisfied? Look Beyond Mayweather and Pacquiao
description: The fight of the century did not live up to expectations, but some lesser-known boxers are fighting in the near future with a good chance to produce some exciting bouts.

title: Israeli Foreign Minister Says He Won’t Join Netanyahu’s New Government
description: Avigdor Lieberman’s decision is unlikely to block a coalition by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, but it would leave him with a razor-thin majority in Parliament.

title: First Draft: Today in Politics: Republicans to Increase Their Boots on the Trail
description: The three Republicans announcing presidential bids this week could have an important effect on the party’s political discussion.

title: Israeli President Calls for Calm After Anti-Discrimination Protests in Tel Aviv
description: President Reuven Rivlin said that demonstrations by Ethiopian-Israelis had “revealed an open and raw wound at the heart of Israeli society,” but he condemned the violence.

title: City Room: New York Today: One, Two, Tree
description: Monday: Counting trees, very warm weather, and echoes of Brownsville.
